    dc:creator "Balkenohl, Michael" ;
    dc:date "2022" ;
    dc:title "On the female gonocoxites of Asian, Arabian, and African Clivinini with realignment of the Thliboclivina-, Physoclivina-, and Eoclivina-species groups, and notes on the higher systematics of the tribe Clivinini Rafinesque, 1815 (Coleoptera, Carabidae)" ;
    fabio:hasPart <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.7119961> ;
    a fabio:JournalArticle .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.7119961>
    dc:description "FIGURES 3-6. Thliboclivinina species, habitus. 3. Thliboclivina amalita Basilewsky, 1964, specimen from Olibribouo, Ivory Coast. 4. Physoclivina physopleura (Burgeon, 1935), PT from Lukula, Congo. 5. Eoclivina dumolinii (Putzeys, 1846), specimen from Kumasi, Ghana. 6. Sulciclivina attenuata (Herbst, 1806), specimen from Kalam, Swat." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/7119961/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

